#!/usr/bin/env Rscript

# =============================================================================
# PESTFLY — Step 5: Random Forest origin-tracing validation
# =============================================================================
#
# Purpose
# -------
# Step 5 provides an independent machine-learning corroboration of the Step 4
# hierarchical SNP-based origin assignment.
#
# Step 4 remains the primary origin-tracing step.
# Step 5 is an orthogonal validation layer.
#
# Step 5 trains Random Forest classifiers on reference samples using the SNP
# matrices generated by Step 3, then:
#
#   1. evaluates reference classification performance by repeated stratified
#      k-fold cross-validation;
#
#   2. predicts query/intercept samples independently of the Step 4 Bayesian
#      multi-K assignment;
#
#   3. reports whether Random Forest predictions support, contradict, or remain
#      uncertain relative to the Step 4 interpretation.
#
# =============================================================================
# Conceptual relationship with Steps 4 and 4b
# =============================================================================
#
# Step 4:
#   Main hierarchical Bayesian-like likelihood assignment.
#   Uses multi-K stability, posterior probability, posterior gap, global K
#   agreement, and large-K tail agreement.
#
# Step 4b:
#   Leave-one-out validation of the Step 4 assignment logic on reference samples.
#
# Step 5:
#   Independent Random Forest validation.
#
# Random Forest does not use the Step 4 multi-K likelihood model. Instead, it
# learns classification rules from the same Step 3 SNP matrices and evaluates
# whether the same origin signal is recoverable with a different statistical
# framework.
#
# Therefore:
#
#   - concordance between Step 4 and Step 5 supports the assignment;
#   - discordance should be inspected, especially for subregion-level calls;
#   - Step 5 should not overrule Step 4 automatically.
#
# =============================================================================
# Default panels
# =============================================================================
#
#   P1: macroregion_3 Africa vs Asia
#   P2: subregion within Africa
#   P3: subregion within Asia
#
# P4 population-level assignment is not used in the default workflow.
#
# Interpretation:
#
#   - P1 RF predictions are relevant for all query samples.
#   - P2 RF predictions should only be interpreted for samples assigned to Africa
#     by Step 4.
#   - P3 RF predictions should only be interpreted for samples assigned to Asia
#     by Step 4.
#
# =============================================================================
# Inputs
# =============================================================================
#
# Required:
#
#   results/01_qc/metadata_clean.tsv
#   results/02_snp_panels/panels/<panel_id>/snp_matrix.rds
#   results/02_snp_panels/panels/<panel_id>/snp_map.tsv
#
# Optional:
#
#   results/04_origin_assignment/final_assignment.tsv
#
# If present, Step 4 calls are merged into the Step 5 query-prediction table.
#
# =============================================================================
# Outputs
# =============================================================================
#
# Written to:
#
#   results/06_rf_corroboration/
#
# Main outputs:
#
#   step5_rf_panels_index.tsv / .rds
#   RF_all_panels_predictions_queries.tsv / .rds
#   RF_all_panels_cv_summary.tsv / .rds
#   RF_all_panels_cv_perclass.tsv / .rds
#   step5_random_forest_summary.xlsx
#   step5_run_info.rds
#
# Per-panel outputs:
#
#   RF_<panel>_predictions_queries.tsv
#   RF_<panel>_cv_summary.tsv
#   RF_<panel>_cv_perclass.tsv
#   RF_<panel>_cv_rows.tsv
#   RF_<panel>_variable_importance.tsv
#   FIG_RF_<panel>_validation_A4.pdf
#
# =============================================================================
# Run
# =============================================================================
#
#   Rscript steps/step5_random_forest_origin_tracing/run.R
#
# Optional:
#
#   Rscript steps/step5_random_forest_origin_tracing/run.R --cores 8 --trees 1000
#
# =============================================================================

suppressPackageStartupMessages({
  library(optparse)
  library(data.table)
